Five men will appear in the Musina Magistrates Court on Monday, 27 February. The men were found with illegal cigarettes worth over R30 million at a farm between Musina and the Beitbridge Port of Entry on Saturday, 25 February. According to the Hawks' Serious Commercial Crime Investigation, they received a tip-off about illegal cigarettes that were kept at a farm waiting to be transported to different destinations. Hawks spokesman Captain Matimba Maluleke said a sting operation between the was immediately conducted. He said when the team arrived at the identified farm, they found a truck and a tractor with the trailer loaded with suspected illegal cigarettes that were covered with brick pallets. ALSO READ: Guards shot during heist “A preliminary investigation led to the discovery of a bakkie and another truck in the vicinity that were also fully loaded with suspected illegal cigarettes. The value of the seized suspected illegal cigarettes is over R30 million.” You must be SIGNED IN to read comments “The team worked throughout the night trying to safeguard the exhibit and locate the suspects,” he said. Maluleke said eventually, five suspects aged between 26 and 44 were arrested for contravening the Customs and Excise Act. The National Head of the Hawks, Lieutenant General Godfrey Lebeya has commended the team for a good job. 